text: was a district located in Ishikari Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of 2004, the district had an estimated population of 2,592 and a density of 8.85 persons per km². The total area was 292.84 km². ==Former towns and villages== * Atsuta ==Mergers== * On October 1, 2005, the village of Atsuta, along with the village of Hamamasu (from Hamamasu District), was merged into the expanded city of Ishikari. Category:Former districts of Hokkaido
title: Atsuta District, Hokkaido
